    {
      "id": 175987,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "Social Media Ads is a tool for dedicated paid social specialists working with ads. The tool needs to interact with the user's social network account. To do this, Semrush collects a token to access and modify the advertising data of the social media account. There was a possible ability to brute force ids due to weak id generation by MongoDB. As a result, it was possible to access another user's token. MongoDB Object Ids have the following pattern:\n- а 4-byte timestamp, representing the ObjectId's creation, measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.\n- а 5-byte random value generated once per process. This random value is unique to the machine and process.\n- а 3-byte incrementing counter, initialized to a random value.\n\n",
      "updated_at": "2022-08-04T13:44:32.785Z",
